OL,3,CMore than 4,500 police officers
OL,4,Cspecially trained to investigate rape
OL,6,FThe training means victims of "often
OL,7,Fcomplex" offences will "receive better
OL,8,Fsupport throughout the process as
OL,9,Ftheir perpetrators are brought to
OL,10,Fjustice", the Home Office said.
OL,12,FIt comes after the Prime Minister was
OL,13,Fforced to reject claims that rape had
OL,14,Feffectively become "decriminalised".
OL,15,FRishi Sunak instead insisted that
OL,16,Fimprovements had been made in police
OL,17,Fprobes.
