OL,6,FThe Victims' Commissioner for England
OL,7,Fand Wales, Baroness Newlove, said the
OL,8,Ftraining was a "positive step towards
OL,9,Fa more supportive criminal justice
OL,10,Fsystem for victims of rape and sexual
OL,11,Fassault".
OL,13,FBut she stressed it was "vital" the
OL,14,FCrown Prosecution Service and police
OL,15,Fcontinued to work together to make
OL,16,Fsure the work has "lasting impact" as
OL,17,Fshe called for "sustained resourcing
OL,18,Fand leadership" to be dedicated to the
OL,19,Fprogramme long term.
